# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- In lexicographically ordered dictionary we don't have any words less in value after greater.
- So we don't need to traverse $$words$$ array $$n^2$$ times just check it for $$n$$ times.
- if $$current word[i]$$ is greater in size of $$currentword[i+1]$$ and  next word is having less value according to orders then return false
- else check for every word pair in one iteration from i=0 to i=n-1
- because for $$nth$$ word we will check at $$n-1'th$$ tearm
- proceed further till we match in pair of $$words[i]$$ and $$words[i+1]$$
- when not matched check $$current$$ $$alphabet$$ $$order$$ in $$words[i]$$ and $$words[i+1]$$
- if it's not according to given order then return false
- else at last return true

